      <div resp="part:emfr" type="translation">
        <p n="1-4">
      			Tirthy-eight <supplied reason="subaudible">year</supplied> of the victorious king Mahendravarman<note>May<choice>
              <orig>I</orig>
              <reg>yi</reg>
            </choice>ntiraparumaṉ the original Tamil.</note>.</p>
        <p n="4-9">
      			<supplied reason="subaudible">This is</supplied> the stone <supplied reason="subaudible">of</supplied> Kākaṇṭi Aṇṇāvaṉ, the servant of Poṉṉarampaṉār, he who fell recapturing <supplied reason="explanation">
            <foreign>iṭuvittu</foreign>
            <note>That is (?), <foreign>viṭuvittu</foreign>, literally "liberating".</note>
          </supplied> cattle when Kantaviṇṇaṉār, the nephew of the royal Bāṇa king seized cattle <supplied reason="subaudible">in</supplied> kūṭal.	
      		</p>
        <p n="10-12">
      			<supplied reason="subaudible">This is</supplied> stone that the <seg cert="low">people</seg> <supplied reason="explanation">
            <foreign>iḷa-makkaḷ</foreign>
            <note><bibl>
                <ptr target="bib:Mahalingam1988_01"/>
              </bibl> suggests to translate as "soldiers".</note>
          </supplied> of Kūṭal had planted.
      		</p>
